	abstract = {Conducting research can feel like finding the proverbial needle in a haystack. Discussing with different individuals how they conduct research, the process varies from the tentative approach used by first semester college student to the finetuned methodology wielded by a seasoned tenure track professor. When talking more in-depth with emeritus faculty, even they reminiscence on starting in the shelves to moving to resources on CDs to sifting through articles in databases to dipping a toe in the artificial intelligence waters. The tools and methodology adopted by emeritus faculty depending on their field altered significantly during the span of their career. With AI being touted in mainstream media and AI conferences stepping out into the limelight in academia, the question "How can using AI tools time save time, act in a supporting role, uncover unknowns, or remove barriers for STEM researchers?" can be asked. This book chapter uncovers practical ways to approach utilizing AI in the scientific method from the beginning of the research process to end. With the exponentially increasing number of different AI tools, software, and apps proliferating the research landscape and their rapid evolution in terms of features and accuracy, the chapter is a moment in time unveiling possibilities. © 2025 Walter de Gruyter GmbH. All rights reserved.},
