	abstract = {The integration of Artificial Intelligence (AI) into STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics) education has the potential to revolutionize how these disciplines are taught, learned, and applied. This chapter explores the evolving role of AI in shaping STEM education through personalized learning, adaptive assessments, and virtual laboratories. It examines the implications of AI-driven tools on curriculum design and pedagogical strategies, highlighting how these technologies foster critical thinking, problem-solving, and innovation. Moreover, the chapter investigates how AI can bridge the gap between educational outcomes and industry demands, equipping students with the technical and interdisciplinary skills necessary for success in the AIdriven workforce. Ethical considerations, challenges of implementation, and strategies to address inequities in access to AI-enhanced learning are also discussed. This chapter ultimately envisions a future where AI serves as a catalyst for equity, creativity, and excellence in STEM education. © 2026, IGI Global Scientific Publishing. All rights reserved.},
